1
00:01:32,080 --> 00:01:34,970
[How dare you!?]

2
00:01:35,009 --> 00:01:37,960
[Episode 11]

3
00:02:00,120 --> 00:02:01,180
Where's the money?

4
00:02:02,790 --> 00:02:04,510
Where's the money in the treasury?

5
00:02:04,510 --> 00:02:06,770
Where's the money of Great Xia's people?

6
00:02:07,690 --> 00:02:08,490
Your Majesty.

7
00:02:09,250 --> 00:02:11,310
Your Majesty, please let me explain.

8
00:02:11,400 --> 00:02:12,910
This is all problems left by

9
00:02:12,910 --> 00:02:14,840
the previous Minister of Revenue.

10
00:02:15,400 --> 00:02:16,200
Your Majesty.

11
00:02:16,710 --> 00:02:18,240
I have only

12
00:02:18,310 --> 00:02:20,670
just been appointed, Your Majesty!

13
00:02:34,120 --> 00:02:34,920
Your Majesty.

14
00:02:35,870 --> 00:02:37,440
Right General You sent

15
00:02:37,680 --> 00:02:38,400
an urgent report saying...

16
00:02:38,400 --> 00:02:39,200
Speak louder!

17
00:02:40,560 --> 00:02:40,910
Yes!

18
00:02:43,590 --> 00:02:44,120
Right...

19
00:02:45,560 --> 00:02:47,710
Right General You
has sent an urgent report

20
00:02:47,710 --> 00:02:50,240
saying the military rations
have gone moldy!

21
00:03:02,150 --> 00:03:02,490
[Your subject submits the following...]

22
00:03:02,830 --> 00:03:04,000
[State matters rest on rites and war;
yet the frontiers are now in peril.]

23
00:03:04,000 --> 00:03:06,610
[The enemy watches as our troops starve,
their morale and provisions exhausted.]

24
00:03:06,610 --> 00:03:07,610
[I fear a coup if this persists;
my heart burns with restless anxiety.]

25
00:03:12,570 --> 00:03:13,970
They're threatening me.

26
00:03:14,980 --> 00:03:17,310
They say if the rations aren't increased,

27
00:03:18,930 --> 00:03:21,190
they won't be able to defend the borders.

28
00:03:22,850 --> 00:03:25,079
Even my own army dares to threaten me.

29
00:03:27,430 --> 00:03:29,230
The mausoleum needs to be built.

30
00:03:30,630 --> 00:03:33,030
The military rations need to be increased.

31
00:03:33,950 --> 00:03:35,690
But the treasury is empty!

32
00:03:36,430 --> 00:03:37,620
Empty!

33
00:03:39,290 --> 00:03:40,390
Empty, empty...

34
00:03:51,620 --> 00:03:54,350
Tell me, is it time this kingdom
changes its name?

35
00:03:55,210 --> 00:03:56,680
Your Majesty, I deserve to die!

36
00:03:56,680 --> 00:03:57,530
I deserve to die!

37
00:03:57,530 --> 00:03:58,460
I deserve to die!

38
00:03:58,710 --> 00:03:59,310
I deserve—

39
00:04:04,070 --> 00:04:07,600
The problem isn't solved
and you're already thinking of dying?

40
00:04:07,630 --> 00:04:08,560
Then I won't die.

41
00:04:08,900 --> 00:04:09,560
I won't die.

42
00:04:09,680 --> 00:04:10,610
Here's the deal.

43
00:04:11,780 --> 00:04:13,710
If you can replenish the treasury,

44
00:04:14,880 --> 00:04:16,490
I'll leave your body intact.

45
00:04:17,079 --> 00:04:18,510
-If not…
-Your Majesty—

46
00:04:18,930 --> 00:04:20,529
Your entire family

47
00:04:21,510 --> 00:04:23,330
will go join your dear brother.

48
00:04:24,000 --> 00:04:24,470
Well...

49
00:04:25,620 --> 00:04:26,620
No, Your Majesty!

50
00:04:28,120 --> 00:04:29,450
Spare me, Your Majesty!

51
00:04:29,730 --> 00:04:30,530
Your Majesty.

52
00:04:30,690 --> 00:04:31,300
Your Majesty.

53
00:04:31,300 --> 00:04:32,100
Your Majesty.

54
00:04:34,070 --> 00:04:35,070
Your Majesty.

55
00:04:40,420 --> 00:04:41,830
What do I do?

56
00:04:43,120 --> 00:04:45,230
Your Highness, this is a brilliant idea.

57
00:04:45,230 --> 00:04:46,500
To have General You

58
00:04:46,680 --> 00:04:49,390
claim the rations are moldy
at this critical moment.

59
00:04:49,390 --> 00:04:50,810
His Majesty is furious.

60
00:04:51,270 --> 00:04:52,510
Right now, the Ministry of Revenue

61
00:04:52,510 --> 00:04:54,190
is in complete chaos.

62
00:04:55,190 --> 00:04:58,630
Along with the starving people blocking
the imperial carriage this morning,

63
00:04:58,630 --> 00:05:00,360
the Empress Dowager's faction

64
00:05:00,410 --> 00:05:02,320
won't have it easy anymore.

65
00:05:04,360 --> 00:05:07,540
Do you think those starving people
blocking the carriage

66
00:05:07,540 --> 00:05:08,500
was an accident?

67
00:05:12,260 --> 00:05:13,320
It was His Majesty.

68
00:05:14,870 --> 00:05:16,360
His Majesty planned

69
00:05:16,480 --> 00:05:18,560
to make an example
of the Ministry of Revenue.

70
00:05:18,560 --> 00:05:20,960
He previously used
his madness as an excuse

71
00:05:21,630 --> 00:05:24,030
to execute the former Minister of Revenue.

72
00:05:24,950 --> 00:05:28,350
Unfortunately,
it didn't shake the ministry's foundation.

73
00:05:29,570 --> 00:05:31,570
But now the situation is different.

74
00:05:33,190 --> 00:05:34,190
Military matters

75
00:05:35,720 --> 00:05:36,980
and civilian affairs—

76
00:05:37,800 --> 00:05:39,810
they're all concerning
the fate of the kingdom.

77
00:05:39,810 --> 00:05:42,270
The Ministry of Revenue
can't escape responsibility.

78
00:05:42,270 --> 00:05:42,920
Right now they're

79
00:05:42,920 --> 00:05:45,250
also in charge of building the mausoleum.

80
00:05:46,480 --> 00:05:48,680
If they can't fill this financial hole,

81
00:05:49,390 --> 00:05:51,390
it's like digging their own graves.

82
00:05:52,000 --> 00:05:52,560
But His Majesty

83
00:05:52,560 --> 00:05:55,360
chose this exact moment
to strike at the Ministry.

84
00:05:58,920 --> 00:06:00,390
It seems our Emperor

85
00:06:01,630 --> 00:06:02,920
has made this move

86
00:06:03,950 --> 00:06:05,610
with careful consideration.

87
00:06:05,950 --> 00:06:06,830
But it's a pity.

88
00:06:08,030 --> 00:06:09,270
What's a pity?

89
00:06:10,070 --> 00:06:12,980
Just handling this current situation
isn't enough.

90
00:06:12,980 --> 00:06:14,070
More importantly,

91
00:06:14,750 --> 00:06:17,330
once Chen Danian
can't handle the pressure,

92
00:06:17,750 --> 00:06:19,750
the position of Minister of Revenue

93
00:06:20,590 --> 00:06:21,740
will become vacant.

94
00:06:22,160 --> 00:06:23,270
Then people on our side

95
00:06:23,270 --> 00:06:24,860
can fill that vacancy.

96
00:06:26,480 --> 00:06:27,720
Congratulations, Your Highness.

97
00:06:27,720 --> 00:06:30,310
With both wealth and military power,

98
00:06:30,540 --> 00:06:32,940
you won't be held back
by anyone anymore.

99
00:06:33,800 --> 00:06:34,590
But...

100
00:06:35,159 --> 00:06:36,560
if the Empress Dowager

101
00:06:36,800 --> 00:06:38,210
wants to protect the Ministry of Revenue

102
00:06:38,210 --> 00:06:40,920
and is willing to use
the funds for the mausoleum

103
00:06:41,000 --> 00:06:42,430
to supplement the military provisions,

104
00:06:42,430 --> 00:06:43,000
then...

105
00:06:44,040 --> 00:06:45,840
If you were the Empress Dowager,

106
00:06:48,240 --> 00:06:51,190
and this puppet
you've controlled for over a decade

107
00:06:52,600 --> 00:06:54,659
suddenly developed a mind of his own,

108
00:06:57,670 --> 00:06:59,659
would you compromise,

109
00:07:01,000 --> 00:07:02,350
bide your time,

110
00:07:03,360 --> 00:07:04,760
or confront him directly

111
00:07:06,600 --> 00:07:08,480
and refuse to back down?

112
00:07:08,830 --> 00:07:10,270
Please give us your guidance

113
00:07:10,270 --> 00:07:12,330
on what should be done,
Your Majesty.

114
00:07:12,680 --> 00:07:15,000
I truly have no solutions left.

115
00:07:15,600 --> 00:07:17,530
These past few days I've been so worried

116
00:07:17,530 --> 00:07:20,360
that I can't sleep or eat properly.

117
00:07:20,830 --> 00:07:22,000
I fear making a mistake

118
00:07:22,000 --> 00:07:24,600
ruining your important affairs,
Your Majesty.

119
00:07:24,600 --> 00:07:27,670
Lord Chen.

120
00:07:28,240 --> 00:07:29,890
The treasury deficit

121
00:07:30,040 --> 00:07:32,250
is indeed not sustainable.

122
00:07:33,159 --> 00:07:34,620
Those military officials

123
00:07:34,870 --> 00:07:36,570
only know how to fight

124
00:07:36,920 --> 00:07:40,140
and are simple-minded,
only caring about money in hand.

125
00:07:41,070 --> 00:07:42,340
If their provisions

126
00:07:42,920 --> 00:07:44,450
are delayed even slightly,

127
00:07:44,950 --> 00:07:47,280
the military camp will be in chaos.

128
00:07:47,430 --> 00:07:48,510
Exactly!

129
00:07:49,950 --> 00:07:51,480
So our immediate plan

130
00:07:52,680 --> 00:07:54,540
should be to keep them satisfied.

131
00:07:57,240 --> 00:07:58,700
The military provisions—

132
00:07:59,570 --> 00:08:00,860
approve it for them.

133
00:08:01,350 --> 00:08:02,910
Your Majesty is wise!

134
00:08:03,600 --> 00:08:04,400
Your Majesty,

135
00:08:04,680 --> 00:08:05,810
with your approval,

136
00:08:05,920 --> 00:08:08,120
we can finally stabilize the military.

137
00:08:09,000 --> 00:08:09,560
However,

138
00:08:12,390 --> 00:08:13,190
Your Majesty,

139
00:08:13,390 --> 00:08:14,590
as for the mausoleum—

140
00:08:14,680 --> 00:08:16,390
could it be postponed for a while?

141
00:08:16,390 --> 00:08:17,250
-Nonsense!
-I—

142
00:08:18,870 --> 00:08:20,800
We've already agreed to build it,

143
00:08:21,510 --> 00:08:22,630
and now you want to cancel it?

144
00:08:22,630 --> 00:08:23,720
If we go back on our word,

145
00:08:23,720 --> 00:08:25,570
we will become a laughing stock!

146
00:08:25,850 --> 00:08:28,050
How can the royal family be humiliated?

147
00:08:28,480 --> 00:08:30,050
How can I

148
00:08:30,680 --> 00:08:32,080
be humiliated?

149
00:08:33,600 --> 00:08:34,059
Well...

150
00:08:34,270 --> 00:08:34,549
I...

151
00:08:35,320 --> 00:08:36,289
I understand.

152
00:08:36,360 --> 00:08:36,760
But...

153
00:08:37,669 --> 00:08:39,799
But both projects require money,

154
00:08:39,940 --> 00:08:40,960
and I really

155
00:08:41,240 --> 00:08:44,090
can't cook without rice, Empress Dowager.

156
00:08:44,360 --> 00:08:45,550
Lord Chen.

157
00:08:46,120 --> 00:08:48,530
You are the Minister of Revenue,

158
00:08:48,730 --> 00:08:50,910
in charge of the empire's finances.

159
00:08:51,670 --> 00:08:54,280
That's your responsibility.

160
00:08:54,630 --> 00:08:56,590
Use your brain

161
00:08:56,630 --> 00:08:58,430
and find a solution.

162
00:08:59,120 --> 00:09:01,080
Learn from your brother.

163
00:09:03,160 --> 00:09:03,960
Your Majesty!

164
00:09:04,100 --> 00:09:04,770
Your Majesty!

165
00:09:04,770 --> 00:09:05,620
Your Majesty!

166
00:09:09,590 --> 00:09:11,690
What do I do?

167
00:09:14,180 --> 00:09:16,840
I shouldn't have taken over this mess!

168
00:09:17,240 --> 00:09:18,890
There's no profit to be made,

169
00:09:19,000 --> 00:09:20,770
and I even have to use my own money!

170
00:09:20,770 --> 00:09:22,970
I wouldn't mind if I could afford it!

171
00:09:23,280 --> 00:09:26,680
But building a mausoleum
and buying military provisions...

172
00:09:26,890 --> 00:09:28,520
Even if I sold you,

173
00:09:28,640 --> 00:09:30,030
all of you and myself too,

174
00:09:30,030 --> 00:09:30,950
all of us,

175
00:09:31,200 --> 00:09:32,960
a thousand times over,

176
00:09:33,480 --> 00:09:35,210
it still wouldn't be enough!

177
00:09:40,130 --> 00:09:42,140
[Yan millet Promotion]

178
00:09:42,170 --> 00:09:45,760
[People] [Ministry of Revenue]
[Empress Dowager] [Prince Duan]

179
00:09:45,780 --> 00:09:49,230
[Scholars]

180
00:09:45,870 --> 00:09:46,870
Empress Dowager,

181
00:09:47,200 --> 00:09:49,060
is having a hard time thanks to me.

182
00:09:49,980 --> 00:09:51,310
The Minister of Revenue

183
00:09:51,910 --> 00:09:52,840
also broke down.

184
00:09:54,100 --> 00:09:55,430
What about Prince Duan?

185
00:09:55,910 --> 00:09:57,960
I heard that officials were summoned
batch after batch

186
00:09:57,960 --> 00:09:59,750
for a meeting among the elites.

187
00:10:01,490 --> 00:10:02,380
So,

188
00:10:03,430 --> 00:10:04,440
it's almost time.

189
00:10:07,790 --> 00:10:09,360
It's time for Li Yunxi

190
00:10:09,920 --> 00:10:11,680
to help us at the critical time.

191
00:10:25,280 --> 00:10:26,660
Such pitiful crying.

192
00:10:27,910 --> 00:10:28,910
What are you waiting for, Li?

193
00:10:28,910 --> 00:10:30,050
I've prepared the gift box.

194
00:10:30,050 --> 00:10:31,550
Let's go meet the Minister of Revenue now.

195
00:10:31,550 --> 00:10:32,350
Wait a moment.

196
00:10:33,870 --> 00:10:35,120
Is this your idea

197
00:10:35,240 --> 00:10:36,840
of persuading the Minister?

198
00:10:37,030 --> 00:10:37,830
What's wrong?

199
00:10:38,030 --> 00:10:39,200
Using the pretext of offering advice

200
00:10:39,200 --> 00:10:40,800
while actually bribing him?

201
00:10:42,340 --> 00:10:44,200
When it comes
to what His Majesty asks for,

202
00:10:44,200 --> 00:10:45,390
as long as we can accomplish it,

203
00:10:45,390 --> 00:10:46,720
the means don't matter.

204
00:10:47,200 --> 00:10:48,550
If we resort to such tactics,

205
00:10:48,550 --> 00:10:51,800
I'd rather not even propose
the Salt-for-Services Policy.

206
00:10:51,800 --> 00:10:53,150
Have you forgotten, Li,

207
00:10:53,200 --> 00:10:55,250
how we obtained our positions?

208
00:10:55,840 --> 00:10:57,510
The gift box
is just to get our foot in the door.

209
00:10:57,510 --> 00:10:59,200
Do you think His Majesty
would really mind?

210
00:10:59,200 --> 00:11:00,460
A wise ruler and honest ministers

211
00:11:00,460 --> 00:11:01,790
are the blessing of a nation.

212
00:11:01,790 --> 00:11:03,120
If the Emperor doesn't care,

213
00:11:03,120 --> 00:11:04,720
that's his failure as a ruler.

214
00:11:04,720 --> 00:11:06,750
If we don't care either, we're shameless

215
00:11:06,750 --> 00:11:07,650
and unworthy of being officials.

216
00:11:07,650 --> 00:11:09,510
Then how do you plan to present it?

217
00:11:09,860 --> 00:11:11,240
Show your scholarly integrity

218
00:11:11,240 --> 00:11:12,900
and give him a harsh scolding?

219
00:11:13,000 --> 00:11:13,820
That's about right.

220
00:11:13,820 --> 00:11:15,150
In this whole world,

221
00:11:15,200 --> 00:11:16,510
there is no one

222
00:11:16,630 --> 00:11:18,850
more upright and honorable than you.

223
00:11:19,000 --> 00:11:20,060
I'll be the villain

224
00:11:20,120 --> 00:11:21,120
in this scenario.

225
00:11:21,210 --> 00:11:22,540
What do you mean by that?

226
00:11:22,720 --> 00:11:24,960
The implementation
of the Salt-for-Services Policy is urgent.

227
00:11:24,960 --> 00:11:26,670
If you can set aside your reservations,

228
00:11:26,670 --> 00:11:27,750
then come with me.

229
00:11:28,030 --> 00:11:28,690
Otherwise,

230
00:11:29,320 --> 00:11:31,240
don't blame me for taking the credit.

231
00:11:31,240 --> 00:11:32,840
Who cares about damn credit?

232
00:11:33,270 --> 00:11:35,080
If you want me to go with you,
leave the gift box behind.

233
00:11:35,080 --> 00:11:35,440
Fine.

234
00:11:35,970 --> 00:11:36,230
[Salt-for-Services Policy]

235
00:11:36,430 --> 00:11:42,020
[Minister of Revenue's Mansion]

236
00:11:36,870 --> 00:11:38,200
What do you mean "fine"?

237
00:11:39,120 --> 00:11:39,450
What—

238
00:11:40,720 --> 00:11:41,120
Er Lan!

239
00:11:42,120 --> 00:11:43,250
How inappropriate!

240
00:11:44,050 --> 00:11:44,700
Listen.

241
00:11:44,830 --> 00:11:46,630
No one will open the door for you.

242
00:11:48,270 --> 00:11:49,530
The door is not closed.

243
00:11:51,120 --> 00:11:52,350
How inappropriate!

244
00:11:53,160 --> 00:11:54,090
Master! Master!

245
00:11:56,040 --> 00:11:56,510
Master!

246
00:11:56,960 --> 00:11:58,710
Lord Er from the Ministry of Revenue
requests to see you.

247
00:11:58,710 --> 00:11:59,670
I won't see anyone!

248
00:11:59,670 --> 00:12:01,360
I don't want to see anyone right now!

249
00:12:01,360 --> 00:12:03,690
But he says he has a way
to solve Your Lordship's predicament.

250
00:12:03,690 --> 00:12:04,320
Nonsense!

251
00:12:04,910 --> 00:12:06,790
If I, the Minister of Revenue,
cannot solve it—

252
00:12:06,790 --> 00:12:09,080
something even the Empress Dowager
and His Majesty cannot solve—

253
00:12:09,080 --> 00:12:10,440
how can he possibly have a solution?

254
00:12:10,440 --> 00:12:11,300
I won't see him!

255
00:12:11,750 --> 00:12:14,310
But he doesn't seem to be joking.

256
00:12:22,390 --> 00:12:23,990
What did you say his name was?

257
00:12:24,750 --> 00:12:27,150
The court can recruit merchants

258
00:12:27,600 --> 00:12:29,520
to supply military provisions.

259
00:12:29,860 --> 00:12:32,320
The court will pay merchants
not with money

260
00:12:32,790 --> 00:12:34,870
but with
Salt Transportation and Sales Licenses.

261
00:12:34,870 --> 00:12:36,000
With these licenses,

262
00:12:36,000 --> 00:12:37,200
merchants...

263
00:12:37,270 --> 00:12:38,910
Can distribute official salt

264
00:12:38,910 --> 00:12:40,470
and profit from trade.

265
00:12:42,480 --> 00:12:45,000
The world bustles for profit

266
00:12:45,390 --> 00:12:47,360
and the world rushes for gain.

267
00:12:47,750 --> 00:12:49,680
With such solid profit prospects,

268
00:12:50,000 --> 00:12:51,840
they will eagerly participate.

269
00:12:52,320 --> 00:12:53,270
In this way,

270
00:12:53,840 --> 00:12:55,970
the court need not drain the treasury.

271
00:12:56,150 --> 00:12:57,710
Through the merchants,

272
00:12:57,820 --> 00:12:59,600
we can solve the provisions problem.

273
00:12:59,600 --> 00:13:01,000
We can support the armies

274
00:13:01,200 --> 00:13:02,360
and still have resources

275
00:13:02,360 --> 00:13:03,760
to repair the mausoleum.

276
00:13:04,720 --> 00:13:05,520
This is called

277
00:13:06,000 --> 00:13:07,800
the Salt-for-Services Policy.

278
00:13:18,120 --> 00:13:18,920
Your Majesty,

279
00:13:19,390 --> 00:13:21,610
salt reform is of great importance.

280
00:13:21,910 --> 00:13:24,060
One move affects everything.

281
00:13:24,390 --> 00:13:26,870
Salt tax is fundamental to the treasury.

282
00:13:27,120 --> 00:13:29,750
Salt trade involves many factions.

283
00:13:29,960 --> 00:13:33,150
Never before
has there been such a bold measure.

284
00:13:33,400 --> 00:13:35,680
Any misstep could cause chaos.

285
00:13:35,900 --> 00:13:38,550
We must not decide rashly.

286
00:13:42,500 --> 00:13:43,500
My dear minister,

287
00:13:44,430 --> 00:13:45,690
you make a valid point.

288
00:13:46,460 --> 00:13:48,160
The regulations can be gradually refined.

289
00:13:48,160 --> 00:13:50,390
But salt reform will benefit
both the military and agriculture

290
00:13:50,390 --> 00:13:51,750
tremendously!

291
00:13:52,270 --> 00:13:53,840
Once the Salt-for-Services Policy
is implemented,

292
00:13:53,840 --> 00:13:55,120
merchants will have profits,

293
00:13:55,120 --> 00:13:56,680
the Empress Dowager's mausoleum
can be repaired,

294
00:13:56,680 --> 00:13:59,630
the frontline will be
sufficiently supplied with provisions,

295
00:13:59,630 --> 00:14:01,000
and the people's corvée and taxes

296
00:14:01,000 --> 00:14:02,660
will be reduced accordingly.

297
00:14:02,750 --> 00:14:06,410
This is a brilliant plan
that kills multiple birds with one stone.

298
00:14:12,120 --> 00:14:13,320
Your Majesty is wise!

299
00:14:14,360 --> 00:14:16,230
I believe Your Majesty has the discernment

300
00:14:16,230 --> 00:14:17,110
to recognize

301
00:14:17,360 --> 00:14:19,150
the brilliance of this policy!

302
00:14:21,200 --> 00:14:22,360
The Salt-for-what Policy?

303
00:14:22,360 --> 00:14:24,160
The Salt-for-Services Policy.

304
00:14:28,670 --> 00:14:29,390
I...

305
00:14:36,480 --> 00:14:37,140
approve it.

306
00:14:38,060 --> 00:14:39,860
Your Majesty is wise!

307
00:14:44,920 --> 00:14:49,140
[Prince Duan's Mansion]

308
00:14:46,390 --> 00:14:48,190
The Salt-for-Services Policy.

309
00:14:48,600 --> 00:14:50,030
What a brilliant move.

310
00:14:50,840 --> 00:14:51,910
It seems ordinary,

311
00:14:53,360 --> 00:14:54,400
yet it revives

312
00:14:54,600 --> 00:14:57,030
the Ministry of Revenue's
nearly depleted treasury.

313
00:14:57,030 --> 00:14:59,160
It also wins over a group of merchants.

314
00:15:00,620 --> 00:15:03,150
There must be a smart mastermind
behind this—

315
00:15:03,190 --> 00:15:04,320
not to be underestimated.

316
00:15:04,320 --> 00:15:06,510
There must be an advisor

317
00:15:07,000 --> 00:15:08,860
behind that sly fox, Chen Danian.

318
00:15:09,550 --> 00:15:10,750
If we can find out who it is,

319
00:15:10,750 --> 00:15:12,270
we'll have leverage.

320
00:15:12,440 --> 00:15:13,500
In future actions,

321
00:15:14,320 --> 00:15:16,120
we'll have better odds.

322
00:15:16,960 --> 00:15:17,510
How about

323
00:15:18,070 --> 00:15:20,130
I conduct a discreet investigation?

324
00:15:20,200 --> 00:15:20,800
Forget it.

325
00:15:22,240 --> 00:15:25,550
The Ministry of Revenue is still under
the Empress Dowager's control.

326
00:15:25,550 --> 00:15:27,240
We shouldn't alert them.

327
00:15:29,200 --> 00:15:30,090
Actually,

328
00:15:30,550 --> 00:15:33,010
the Ministry of Revenue's
revival this time

329
00:15:33,510 --> 00:15:34,630
will make His Majesty

330
00:15:34,630 --> 00:15:36,420
the biggest loser.

331
00:15:36,450 --> 00:15:38,490
I saw his face in court—

332
00:15:39,080 --> 00:15:40,320
it looked terrible.

333
00:15:41,770 --> 00:15:43,790
The Empress Dowager didn't win either.

334
00:15:43,790 --> 00:15:44,960
These Salt Transportation
and Sales Licenses

335
00:15:44,960 --> 00:15:46,510
generate so much profit every year.

336
00:15:46,510 --> 00:15:48,570
Just handing it all to the merchants,

337
00:15:48,640 --> 00:15:50,750
her heart must be aching.

338
00:15:53,510 --> 00:15:54,550
In that case,

339
00:15:55,150 --> 00:15:57,720
we'll continue to watch them fight.

340
00:16:00,480 --> 00:16:02,360
Your Highness is wise.

341
00:16:03,080 --> 00:16:04,880
The Salt-for-Services Policy.

342
00:16:05,840 --> 00:16:08,110
What a brilliant policy.

343
00:16:09,520 --> 00:16:10,520
Chen Danian,

344
00:16:11,080 --> 00:16:14,190
you've finally got it.

345
00:16:15,910 --> 00:16:17,480
Thank you for your praise,
Your Majesty.

346
00:16:17,480 --> 00:16:19,110
I will work even harder

347
00:16:19,270 --> 00:16:21,070
to live up to your expectations.

348
00:16:21,200 --> 00:16:21,670
CEO Dan!

349
00:16:25,480 --> 00:16:25,870
Look!

350
00:16:27,590 --> 00:16:29,230
[Yan millet: doesn't rot easily,
making it easier to be stored.]

351
00:16:27,910 --> 00:16:28,990
We made it.

352
00:16:33,460 --> 00:16:37,720
[Yan millet: doesn't rot easily,
making it easier to be stored.] [Approved]

353
00:16:47,720 --> 00:16:50,210
We're distributing free Yan millet seeds!

354
00:16:50,350 --> 00:16:51,700
Everyone can come

355
00:16:51,870 --> 00:16:53,270
and get them for free!

356
00:16:53,550 --> 00:16:54,900
The more you plant...

357
00:16:54,960 --> 00:16:55,720
It's free?

358
00:16:55,720 --> 00:16:57,960
The more tax you can offset next year!

359
00:16:58,030 --> 00:17:00,950
We're distributing free Yan millet seeds!

360
00:17:11,109 --> 00:17:11,440
Here.

361
00:17:11,750 --> 00:17:13,680
The Salt-for-Services Policy
went smoothly.

362
00:17:13,680 --> 00:17:15,069
Let's toast to our heroes,

363
00:17:15,069 --> 00:17:15,599
Wang Zhao

364
00:17:15,819 --> 00:17:16,420
and Er Lan.

365
00:17:17,430 --> 00:17:18,490
I don't deserve it.

366
00:17:18,829 --> 00:17:20,730
Li wrote the script.

367
00:17:21,400 --> 00:17:23,160
I just recited it.

368
00:17:24,220 --> 00:17:25,020
That's right.

369
00:17:25,069 --> 00:17:26,829
The Salt-for-Services Policy
was also Li's idea.

370
00:17:26,829 --> 00:17:28,160
I merely carried it out.

371
00:17:34,920 --> 00:17:36,130
This bowl of wine for Lord Li

372
00:17:36,130 --> 00:17:36,640
is on me.

373
00:17:39,270 --> 00:17:39,600
Come.

374
00:17:44,660 --> 00:17:45,660
Please be seated.

375
00:17:47,240 --> 00:17:49,170
With the treasury in such turmoil,

376
00:17:49,210 --> 00:17:50,310
the Ministry of Revenue

377
00:17:50,310 --> 00:17:52,970
has become fish
on His Majesty's cutting board.

378
00:17:53,590 --> 00:17:56,280
How could Prince Duan miss

379
00:17:56,460 --> 00:17:58,920
this chance
to kick them while they're down?

380
00:17:59,350 --> 00:18:00,510
When the Empress Dowager's faction

381
00:18:00,510 --> 00:18:03,510
faces pressure
from both Prince Duan and His Majesty,

382
00:18:03,750 --> 00:18:05,160
then...

383
00:18:05,880 --> 00:18:08,810
Then bringing the Salt-for-Services Policy
to them

384
00:18:09,070 --> 00:18:11,350
will be like a lifeline
to the Ministry of Revenue.

385
00:18:11,350 --> 00:18:13,640
They all think they're acting
on their own initiative.

386
00:18:13,640 --> 00:18:14,900
Who would have thought

387
00:18:15,000 --> 00:18:17,270
that our true purpose
in orchestrating all this

388
00:18:17,270 --> 00:18:18,530
lies inconspicuously

389
00:18:19,270 --> 00:18:20,630
buried in this list?

390
00:18:21,830 --> 00:18:24,480
Once the merchants profit from
the Salt-for-Services Policy,

391
00:18:24,480 --> 00:18:26,130
to save on grain transportation costs,

392
00:18:26,130 --> 00:18:28,990
they'll hire people
to cultivate the borderlands.

393
00:18:29,150 --> 00:18:32,320
The northwestern area near
Yan State has harsh conditions.

394
00:18:32,320 --> 00:18:33,940
Only Yan millet can survive there.

395
00:18:33,940 --> 00:18:36,940
Naturally, it becomes the first choice
for planting.

396
00:18:43,000 --> 00:18:44,000
It's just that...

397
00:18:46,110 --> 00:18:47,420
they don't know yet.

398
00:18:48,310 --> 00:18:49,110
In the future,

399
00:18:50,090 --> 00:18:52,890
Great Xia will rely
on this life-saving Yan millet

400
00:18:53,010 --> 00:18:54,340
to survive the drought.

401
00:19:02,320 --> 00:19:03,850
Why isn't Lord Cen here yet?

402
00:19:05,070 --> 00:19:06,000
I'll go find him.

403
00:19:06,960 --> 00:19:09,110
♪ The joyful drums ♪

404
00:19:09,110 --> 00:19:11,440
♪ Give joyous beats year after year ♪

405
00:19:11,800 --> 00:19:14,070
-♪ Beautiful dance ♪
-Her Highness...

406
00:19:14,090 --> 00:19:17,240
-♪ Brings the lively day ♪
-Is singing about the people's tough life.

407
00:19:17,240 --> 00:19:19,840
Her Highness is singing
of the good days ahead,

408
00:19:20,270 --> 00:19:21,550
giving us hope.

409
00:19:25,850 --> 00:19:27,030
Please remain seated, my dear ministers.

410
00:19:27,030 --> 00:19:29,030
I'll go keep her company for a while.

411
00:19:36,660 --> 00:19:37,830
Speaking of Cen,

412
00:19:37,850 --> 00:19:40,270
he stays in his experimental fields
every day.

413
00:19:40,270 --> 00:19:42,340
Even His Majesty can't summon him away.

414
00:19:42,340 --> 00:19:43,390
What a fool.

415
00:19:43,830 --> 00:19:45,360
Cen is not a fool.

416
00:19:45,390 --> 00:19:47,720
He's a person of utmost purity and virtue.

417
00:19:47,930 --> 00:19:49,890
Without his cultivation methods,

418
00:19:50,030 --> 00:19:51,510
even if our performance is excellent

419
00:19:51,510 --> 00:19:52,400
and our strategies brilliant,

420
00:19:52,400 --> 00:19:54,110
it would all be like a castle in the air,

421
00:19:54,110 --> 00:19:55,400
without foundation.

422
00:19:55,630 --> 00:19:57,010
Er Lan is right.

423
00:19:58,480 --> 00:20:00,330
That's Lord Er to you.

424
00:20:02,390 --> 00:20:03,720
I haven't congratulated you yet.

425
00:20:03,720 --> 00:20:05,670
You gained the Minister of Rite's favor
so quickly

426
00:20:05,670 --> 00:20:07,230
and received an official promotion.

427
00:20:07,230 --> 00:20:07,790
Lord Er,

428
00:20:08,030 --> 00:20:08,830
I toast to you.

429
00:20:11,380 --> 00:20:12,020
Li.

430
00:20:12,530 --> 00:20:13,300
Li.

431
00:20:14,480 --> 00:20:15,810
I know you're upset, Li.

432
00:20:15,990 --> 00:20:17,240
I had a bad temper that day.

433
00:20:17,240 --> 00:20:18,070
Please don't take offense.

434
00:20:18,070 --> 00:20:19,480
I'll punish myself with a drink.

435
00:20:19,480 --> 00:20:19,940
No need.

436
00:20:21,160 --> 00:20:22,220
A toast from Lord Er

437
00:20:23,070 --> 00:20:24,270
is beyond my station.

438
00:20:24,400 --> 00:20:24,880
Right.

439
00:20:25,790 --> 00:20:27,720
If he hadn't stolen your credit that day,

440
00:20:27,720 --> 00:20:29,180
you'd be the one promoted.

441
00:20:33,080 --> 00:20:35,790
The Salt-for-Services Policy
was Li's idea.

442
00:20:35,820 --> 00:20:37,090
I merely conveyed it.

443
00:20:37,440 --> 00:20:39,200
When His Majesty rewards merit,

444
00:20:39,200 --> 00:20:41,010
he won't forget your contribution, Li.

445
00:20:41,010 --> 00:20:42,210
What won't he forget?

446
00:20:43,270 --> 00:20:45,110
What about me needs to be remembered?

447
00:20:45,110 --> 00:20:46,030
I've said it before—

448
00:20:46,030 --> 00:20:47,630
my ambitions lie elsewhere!

449
00:20:48,000 --> 00:20:48,310
Li.

450
00:20:48,310 --> 00:20:48,910
Step back!

451
00:20:52,490 --> 00:20:54,610
Indeed, Li.

452
00:20:54,790 --> 00:20:55,850
So noble and proud,

453
00:20:55,920 --> 00:20:57,000
with such lofty aspirations.

454
00:20:57,000 --> 00:20:59,400
Ready to join court today
and die tomorrow.

455
00:20:59,440 --> 00:21:02,370
-Is that what you think—
-Indeed that's what I think.

456
00:21:05,300 --> 00:21:05,700
You...

457
00:21:06,200 --> 00:21:06,720
Fine!

458
00:21:07,000 --> 00:21:07,850
I'll live!

459
00:21:08,590 --> 00:21:09,310
Live well.

460
00:21:10,790 --> 00:21:12,060
How inappropriate!

461
00:21:13,890 --> 00:21:16,830
It appears Yan millet
is indeed the most drought-resistant

462
00:21:16,830 --> 00:21:17,890
and grows the best.

463
00:21:17,960 --> 00:21:19,650
Though planted in late autumn

464
00:21:19,790 --> 00:21:21,590
without sufficient irrigation,

465
00:21:21,590 --> 00:21:22,790
in just a month or so,

466
00:21:23,030 --> 00:21:24,230
it's grown this well.

467
00:21:24,720 --> 00:21:25,480
Lord Cen,

468
00:21:25,750 --> 00:21:27,340
could you, like you did before,

469
00:21:27,340 --> 00:21:29,740
determine what soil Yan millet suits best,

470
00:21:29,970 --> 00:21:32,030
and how to irrigate and fertilize it?

471
00:21:37,500 --> 00:21:38,360
I

472
00:21:38,790 --> 00:21:40,250
will certainly do my best.

473
00:21:41,920 --> 00:21:42,570
Lord Cen,

474
00:21:44,000 --> 00:21:45,660
please take care of yourself.

475
00:21:46,510 --> 00:21:48,110
Don't worry, Your Highness.

476
00:21:48,110 --> 00:21:48,720
I

477
00:21:49,160 --> 00:21:51,090
will do my best to live a bit longer.

478
00:21:51,200 --> 00:21:53,280
To spend your remaining life like this,

479
00:21:53,280 --> 00:21:54,080
is it worth it?

480
00:21:57,720 --> 00:21:59,520
I have witnessed with my own eyes

481
00:22:00,000 --> 00:22:02,260
people starving to death during famine.

482
00:22:03,840 --> 00:22:06,920
I've also seen mothers
with their infants in swaddling clothes

483
00:22:06,920 --> 00:22:08,680
who never woke again

484
00:22:09,800 --> 00:22:11,100
while fleeing famine.

485
00:22:13,080 --> 00:22:15,080
Everyone lives in the face of death.

486
00:22:18,710 --> 00:22:20,510
To be able to foresee one's death

487
00:22:21,070 --> 00:22:22,870
might be a blessing in disguise.

488
00:22:25,720 --> 00:22:27,250
However, at the very least,

489
00:22:28,880 --> 00:22:31,140
I do not wish to see
the people of this land

490
00:22:31,480 --> 00:22:32,880
die of starvation again.

491
00:22:41,440 --> 00:22:43,040
When my time comes to depart,

492
00:22:43,730 --> 00:22:45,730
I only wish that where my bones rest,

493
00:22:45,920 --> 00:22:48,120
there will be peace throughout the land

494
00:22:49,000 --> 00:22:50,330
and abundant harvests.

495
00:22:54,240 --> 00:22:54,960
Well said.

496
00:22:55,680 --> 00:22:56,680
Excellently put.

497
00:22:59,550 --> 00:23:00,350
Your Majesty.

498
00:23:00,400 --> 00:23:01,260
Your Highness.

499
00:23:03,270 --> 00:23:03,800
Cen,

500
00:23:04,510 --> 00:23:06,170
it's rare to have everyone gathered today.

501
00:23:06,170 --> 00:23:08,850
Would you be willing to set aside
your agricultural work for a moment

502
00:23:08,850 --> 00:23:10,070
and join us, your old friends,

503
00:23:10,070 --> 00:23:10,920
for a drink?

504
00:23:18,420 --> 00:23:18,880
Please.

505
00:23:33,830 --> 00:23:35,260
When I read the novel,

506
00:23:36,000 --> 00:23:38,310
I enjoyed the exciting grand scenes—

507
00:23:38,920 --> 00:23:39,920
power struggles,

508
00:23:40,440 --> 00:23:41,240
epic battles,

509
00:23:42,440 --> 00:23:45,350
watching protagonists
rise from nothing and turn evil,

510
00:23:45,350 --> 00:23:48,480
and the tearing apart of scoundrels
and scheming women.

511
00:23:48,710 --> 00:23:51,110
When I read "Devil's Favorite Concubine,"

512
00:23:51,270 --> 00:23:52,510
I skipped all the parts

513
00:23:52,510 --> 00:23:53,920
where Cen Jintian was fervently farming

514
00:23:53,920 --> 00:23:54,790
completely.

515
00:23:57,790 --> 00:24:00,120
But after coming to this world, I realized

516
00:24:01,240 --> 00:24:02,260
he was the one

517
00:24:02,960 --> 00:24:05,690
who truly saved
countless people from disaster.

518
00:24:06,400 --> 00:24:07,550
To have such a life

519
00:24:08,750 --> 00:24:10,480
is certainly not a waste, is it?

520
00:24:11,130 --> 00:24:12,590
Don't belittle yourself.

521
00:24:13,190 --> 00:24:13,960
You too are

522
00:24:14,720 --> 00:24:16,380
saving people from disaster.

523
00:24:17,200 --> 00:24:17,640
Me?

524
00:24:20,070 --> 00:24:21,710
Helping the dynasty survive the drought,

525
00:24:21,020 --> 00:24:24,010
♪ Standing in the hurricane,
watching the fire rise ♪

526
00:24:22,640 --> 00:24:23,970
objectively speaking,

527
00:24:24,310 --> 00:24:25,750
you should go down in history.

528
00:24:24,330 --> 00:24:27,030
♪ Dancing on the blade's edge, I thread
through blood, writing my wild ode ♪

529
00:24:27,300 --> 00:24:28,250
♪ I am not one of the gentle ones ♪

530
00:24:28,280 --> 00:24:31,820
♪ How could my thoughts
be tethered to the soft begonia?  ♪

531
00:24:28,960 --> 00:24:29,410
Sure.

532
00:24:31,750 --> 00:24:33,110
I don't want to waste this life either.

533
00:24:33,110 --> 00:24:34,560
♪ Do not speak to me
of what's inappropriate ♪

534
00:24:34,580 --> 00:24:36,060
♪ I am the moral order ♪

535
00:24:36,000 --> 00:24:37,030
According to the original novel

536
00:24:36,210 --> 00:24:39,190
♪ The gleam of the blade
tempers feathers into a phantom Phoenix  ♪

537
00:24:37,510 --> 00:24:40,090
Prince Duan paid the highest price
to ascend the throne.

538
00:24:39,320 --> 00:24:40,240
♪ And these Phoenix bones of mine ♪

539
00:24:40,310 --> 00:24:45,200
♪ Empower me
to pierce through the wind and waves ♪

540
00:24:40,640 --> 00:24:43,240
So I'll defeat him
at the lowest cost possible.

541
00:24:43,510 --> 00:24:43,840
Sure.

542
00:24:45,310 --> 00:24:46,850
Preventing the drought
is just the first step.

543
00:24:46,680 --> 00:24:48,310
♪ Allow me ♪

544
00:24:47,310 --> 00:24:49,000
In the future,
he will wage war against Yan State.

545
00:24:48,360 --> 00:24:50,910
♪ To not linger in shame,
to not give way ♪

546
00:24:50,320 --> 00:24:51,930
One general's success
is built on countless deaths.

547
00:24:51,330 --> 00:24:53,820
♪ To not be faithless,
to not admit defeat ♪

548
00:24:52,590 --> 00:24:54,320
Let's prevent him from fighting at all.

549
00:24:54,320 --> 00:24:57,210
♪ A body of stubborn pride
rises to shout that I ♪

550
00:24:54,960 --> 00:24:55,310
Sure.

551
00:24:55,780 --> 00:24:57,510
I remember some details about Yan State.

552
00:24:57,310 --> 00:24:59,870
♪ Was never a creature
meant for the shallows ♪

553
00:24:57,720 --> 00:24:59,250
This war isn't inevitable.

554
00:24:59,590 --> 00:25:00,160
So,

555
00:25:00,200 --> 00:25:01,270
♪ Allow me ♪

556
00:25:01,310 --> 00:25:02,170
let's do it in a diplomatic way—

557
00:25:01,650 --> 00:25:02,980
♪ To never pause ♪

558
00:25:02,640 --> 00:25:03,400
let's ask for peace negotiations.

559
00:25:03,400 --> 00:25:04,400
♪ Allow me ♪

560
00:25:03,790 --> 00:25:04,310
Sure.

561
00:25:04,580 --> 00:25:05,950
♪ To dare to shatter my bones ♪

562
00:25:06,220 --> 00:25:12,030
♪ Wherever I stand,
I dare to write a legend of glory ♪

563
00:25:06,790 --> 00:25:07,790
Are you laughing?

564
00:25:08,640 --> 00:25:09,300
No, I'm not.

565
00:25:09,880 --> 00:25:10,810
You clearly are.

566
00:25:11,750 --> 00:25:12,880
I just find it absurd

567
00:25:13,640 --> 00:25:15,240
that everything we're doing

568
00:25:15,370 --> 00:25:16,400
is all in a book.

569
00:25:18,600 --> 00:25:19,930
It feels quite surreal.

570
00:25:21,590 --> 00:25:23,190
I've thought about this too.

571
00:25:34,480 --> 00:25:35,680
It feels like a paradox.

572
00:25:34,850 --> 00:25:36,230
♪ Allow me ♪

573
00:25:36,250 --> 00:25:38,700
♪ To not linger in shame,
to not give way ♪

574
00:25:37,510 --> 00:25:38,670
How can you be sure

575
00:25:39,280 --> 00:25:41,710
♪ To not be faithless,
to not admit defeat ♪

576
00:25:40,200 --> 00:25:41,730
that the real world outside

577
00:25:42,200 --> 00:25:43,320
isn't just another novel?

578
00:25:42,280 --> 00:25:45,180
♪ A body of stubborn pride
rises to shout that I ♪

579
00:25:45,210 --> 00:25:47,790
♪ Was never a creature
meant for the shallows ♪

580
00:25:48,230 --> 00:25:49,360
♪ Allow me ♪

581
00:25:48,960 --> 00:25:50,000
I indeed don't know.

582
00:25:49,610 --> 00:25:51,030
♪ To never pause ♪

583
00:25:51,270 --> 00:25:52,320
♪ Allow me ♪

584
00:25:51,610 --> 00:25:52,280
So,

585
00:25:52,650 --> 00:25:54,040
♪ To dare to shatter my bones ♪

586
00:25:53,480 --> 00:25:54,890
how can we be certain

587
00:25:54,290 --> 00:26:02,130
♪ Wherever I stand,
I dare to write a legend of glory ♪

588
00:25:55,720 --> 00:25:57,190
that we truly exist?

589
00:26:01,350 --> 00:26:02,810
No point overthinking it.

590
00:26:03,880 --> 00:26:05,830
Even knowing my fate ends in death,

591
00:26:07,270 --> 00:26:08,730
I still want to accomplish

592
00:26:08,790 --> 00:26:10,190
more things before I die.

593
00:26:10,920 --> 00:26:11,270
Sure.

594
00:26:12,160 --> 00:26:13,820
Why do you keep saying "sure"?

595
00:26:13,960 --> 00:26:14,690
Then I'll say

596
00:26:15,440 --> 00:26:17,370
I'll risk my life to accompany you.

597
00:26:18,520 --> 00:26:19,320
Your Majesty!

598
00:26:21,640 --> 00:26:22,350
What's wrong?

599
00:26:22,350 --> 00:26:23,150
Your Majesty,

600
00:26:23,350 --> 00:26:24,110
we've discovered

601
00:26:24,110 --> 00:26:26,200
someone lurking suspiciously
in the forest.

602
00:26:26,200 --> 00:26:27,110
Though it's just one person,

603
00:26:27,110 --> 00:26:28,440
they are highly skilled in martial arts.

604
00:26:28,440 --> 00:26:30,350
Lord Bei Zhou has gone to deal with them.

605
00:26:30,350 --> 00:26:32,880
He ordered us to escort the two of you
back to the palace first.

606
00:26:32,880 --> 00:26:34,410
Only one assassin was sent.

607
00:26:35,440 --> 00:26:37,900
This doesn't seem
like Prince Duan's style.

608
00:26:39,680 --> 00:26:40,610
Keep them alive.

609
00:26:40,800 --> 00:26:42,070
Have Bei Zhou capture them

610
00:26:42,070 --> 00:26:43,110
for interrogation.

611
00:26:43,110 --> 00:26:45,110
Lord Bei Zhou hasn't beaten him yet.

612
00:26:45,550 --> 00:26:46,000
What?

613
00:27:00,110 --> 00:27:01,510
Was there such a character

614
00:27:01,510 --> 00:27:02,770
in the original novel?

615
00:27:04,030 --> 00:27:05,610
I don't remember there being one.

616
00:27:05,610 --> 00:27:08,740
Bei Zhou is the strongest fighter
in the original story,

617
00:27:09,240 --> 00:27:10,770
never having met his match.

618
00:27:11,400 --> 00:27:13,600
This person who appeared out of nowhere

619
00:27:14,160 --> 00:27:15,480
is quite suspicious.

620
00:28:10,920 --> 00:28:11,850
Keep them alive!

621
00:28:15,890 --> 00:28:16,530
Yes, yes.

622
00:28:16,710 --> 00:28:17,640
Hold your blade!

623
00:28:17,680 --> 00:28:19,640
I'm not an assassin. Can't you tell?

624
00:28:19,640 --> 00:28:21,070
If you were really an assassin,

625
00:28:21,070 --> 00:28:22,870
I would have killed you already.

626
00:28:23,750 --> 00:28:25,310
You wouldn't still be alive.

627
00:28:25,310 --> 00:28:26,040
I surrender.

628
00:28:26,550 --> 00:28:27,610
Isn't that enough?

629
00:28:31,830 --> 00:28:32,490
Who are you?

630
00:28:33,240 --> 00:28:34,240
My surname is Bai.

631
00:28:35,510 --> 00:28:36,570
You can call me Bai.

632
00:28:49,400 --> 00:28:50,000
Sir.

633
00:28:50,510 --> 00:28:51,880
Let's talk things through nicely.

634
00:28:51,880 --> 00:28:53,140
Why are you doing this?

635
00:28:56,030 --> 00:28:56,430
Speak.

636
00:28:57,680 --> 00:28:58,740
Where are you from?

637
00:29:01,960 --> 00:29:02,760
I'll tell you!

638
00:29:03,200 --> 00:29:04,000
The Nameless.

639
00:29:04,440 --> 00:29:05,730
You know the Nameless, right?

640
00:29:05,730 --> 00:29:06,590
He's my master.

641
00:29:07,000 --> 00:29:09,110
My master has been observing the stars

642
00:29:09,110 --> 00:29:09,970
and sent me here

643
00:29:10,060 --> 00:29:10,920
with a message.

644
00:29:11,550 --> 00:29:12,150
It's here.

645
00:29:22,070 --> 00:29:23,870
This is indeed his handwriting.

646
00:29:23,900 --> 00:29:25,160
But I can't understand

647
00:29:25,790 --> 00:29:26,590
what he wrote.

648
00:29:26,750 --> 00:29:28,130
Of course you can't understand.

649
00:29:28,130 --> 00:29:29,420
It's not for you.

650
00:29:29,480 --> 00:29:31,160
It's for the Emperor.

651
00:29:34,070 --> 00:29:35,070
Let me have a look.

652
00:29:40,680 --> 00:29:41,490
Emperor?

653
00:29:42,880 --> 00:29:44,010
You are the Emperor?

654
00:29:44,160 --> 00:29:45,240
A living Emperor!

655
00:29:45,780 --> 00:29:48,450
Master, I saw the living Emperor!

656
00:29:56,930 --> 00:29:58,850
The Imperial Throne finds a new master;

657
00:29:58,850 --> 00:30:00,920
the Polaris restores the light in the sky.

658
00:30:00,920 --> 00:30:02,850
A dark omen of royal blood and ruin;

659
00:30:03,480 --> 00:30:05,610
fortune and calamity hang by a thread.

660
00:30:05,680 --> 00:30:07,340
Five stars align,

661
00:30:07,880 --> 00:30:10,010
amidst despair, great fortune rises.

662
00:30:13,590 --> 00:30:15,920
The Imperial Throne finds a new master...

663
00:30:19,500 --> 00:30:20,540
Oh, god.

664
00:30:20,860 --> 00:30:23,000
This person clearly knows your identity.

665
00:30:23,000 --> 00:30:25,200
We've met someone
with true foresight.

666
00:30:28,550 --> 00:30:29,170
Mr. Bei,

667
00:30:29,680 --> 00:30:31,110
do you know the Nameless?

668
00:30:31,750 --> 00:30:33,410
I've known him for many years.

669
00:30:33,920 --> 00:30:35,520
He's skilled in divination.

670
00:30:36,200 --> 00:30:37,860
All his prophecies come true.

671
00:30:38,330 --> 00:30:40,060
He must be sending this message

672
00:30:40,480 --> 00:30:42,520
because he must have foreseen
that you, Dan,

673
00:30:42,520 --> 00:30:43,980
can safeguard the empire.

674
00:30:46,440 --> 00:30:47,110
This kid

675
00:30:47,770 --> 00:30:49,700
is using techniques taught by him.

676
00:30:49,920 --> 00:30:51,380
He should be trustworthy.

677
00:30:51,590 --> 00:30:52,350
Yes.

678
00:30:55,120 --> 00:30:56,960
Master said you're exceptionally talented.

679
00:30:56,960 --> 00:30:58,400
He told me to learn from you.

680
00:30:58,400 --> 00:30:59,460
You're now serving

681
00:30:59,800 --> 00:31:01,130
as the Emperor's guard?

682
00:31:02,010 --> 00:31:02,760
Let me join!

683
00:31:03,510 --> 00:31:04,910
Bei Zhou alone is enough.

684
00:31:05,550 --> 00:31:06,010
Mr. Bei.

685
00:31:06,620 --> 00:31:07,220
Let him go.

686
00:31:09,830 --> 00:31:11,440
He's a godsent elite soldier.

687
00:31:11,440 --> 00:31:12,550
Mr. Bei vouches for him too.

688
00:31:12,550 --> 00:31:13,810
Won't you reconsider?

689
00:31:14,550 --> 00:31:15,880
Master was being kind

690
00:31:16,110 --> 00:31:17,710
sending me here to serve you.

691
00:31:17,720 --> 00:31:19,050
I'm so good at fighting.

692
00:31:19,110 --> 00:31:20,550
Even if I'm not to be your guard,

693
00:31:20,550 --> 00:31:21,440
I can at least

694
00:31:21,790 --> 00:31:23,450
protect this beautiful lady.

695
00:31:29,770 --> 00:31:31,100
Come with us first then.

696
00:31:32,550 --> 00:31:32,920
Sure!

697
00:31:33,750 --> 00:31:34,440
Untie me.

698
00:31:35,200 --> 00:31:35,660
Mr. Bei.

699
00:31:35,880 --> 00:31:36,570
Did you make this?

700
00:31:36,570 --> 00:31:37,230
-Yes.
-Bro.

701
00:31:37,270 --> 00:31:38,000
-For fun.
-Give me a hand.

702
00:31:38,000 --> 00:31:39,200
-Awesome.
-Untie me.

703
00:31:40,640 --> 00:31:41,090
Hey!

704
00:31:41,510 --> 00:31:42,940
Come on, untie me!

705
00:31:43,310 --> 00:31:44,280
Don't leave!

706
00:31:52,030 --> 00:31:54,830
Didn't you get the message
from the secret guards?

707
00:31:56,920 --> 00:31:57,480
I did.

708
00:31:58,670 --> 00:32:00,130
You didn't want me to come.

709
00:32:00,690 --> 00:32:02,750
But Master kept urging me
to come every day,

710
00:32:02,750 --> 00:32:05,350
saying there'll be endless trouble
if you don't rid of the demonic consort.

711
00:32:05,350 --> 00:32:06,640
I'm caught in the middle.

712
00:32:06,640 --> 00:32:07,770
Can't listen to you,

713
00:32:07,790 --> 00:32:09,520
and can't listen to him either.

714
00:32:11,310 --> 00:32:12,270
Life is tough.

715
00:32:18,880 --> 00:32:19,810
Everywhere I go,

716
00:32:19,920 --> 00:32:20,850
I search around.

717
00:32:21,400 --> 00:32:21,880
These

718
00:32:22,680 --> 00:32:24,740
are all folk remedies for headaches.

719
00:32:24,920 --> 00:32:27,250
Maybe it's time to give up.

720
00:32:27,590 --> 00:32:28,160
No way.

721
00:32:28,590 --> 00:32:30,920
This is one of the tasks
Master assigned me.

722
00:32:30,920 --> 00:32:33,030
Since he predicted
I could help you find the cure,

723
00:32:33,030 --> 00:32:34,030
I definitely can.

724
00:32:37,160 --> 00:32:37,830
Fine.

725
00:32:43,790 --> 00:32:44,340
Here.

726
00:33:00,310 --> 00:33:01,770
Don't you dislike sweets?

727
00:33:02,550 --> 00:33:04,810
Why are there so many snacks in your room?

728
00:33:05,960 --> 00:33:07,490
Specially prepared for me?

729
00:33:11,560 --> 00:33:12,700
[The Imperial Throne finds a new master;
the Polaris restores the light in the sky.
A dark omen of royal blood and ruin;]

730
00:33:12,720 --> 00:33:14,220
[fortune and calamity hang by a thread.
Five stars align,
amidst despair, great fortune rises.]

731
00:33:12,880 --> 00:33:13,810
I never expected

732
00:33:14,020 --> 00:33:15,950
to see Master's little note again.

733
00:33:16,750 --> 00:33:18,010
Good thing you kept it.

734
00:33:18,440 --> 00:33:19,100
Otherwise,

735
00:33:19,720 --> 00:33:21,640
I really couldn't find a reason
to come back.

736
00:33:21,640 --> 00:33:23,350
You've learned to steal from me now.

737
00:33:23,350 --> 00:33:24,790
How can you call it stealing?

738
00:33:24,790 --> 00:33:25,960
I just borrowed it.

739
00:33:26,440 --> 00:33:27,440
It's returned now,

740
00:33:27,440 --> 00:33:28,900
isn't it?

741
00:33:33,960 --> 00:33:35,400
I went through all this trouble

742
00:33:35,400 --> 00:33:36,750
to help you fool

743
00:33:37,070 --> 00:33:38,730
that beautiful lady of yours.

744
00:33:40,830 --> 00:33:41,990
Show some respect.

745
00:33:43,070 --> 00:33:44,330
She's a Noble Consort.

746
00:33:46,400 --> 00:33:47,930
From now on, in front of her,

747
00:33:48,270 --> 00:33:49,600
pretend you just met me.

748
00:33:50,030 --> 00:33:51,490
Don't give anything away.

749
00:33:51,880 --> 00:33:52,370
Okay.

750
00:33:52,550 --> 00:33:53,000
Got it.

751
00:33:58,070 --> 00:33:58,720
So

752
00:33:59,510 --> 00:34:01,640
is she the one you've been waiting for?

753
00:34:05,920 --> 00:34:06,640
No.

754
00:34:07,510 --> 00:34:08,639
It was someone else.

755
00:34:22,760 --> 00:34:24,590
I was waiting for the wrong person.

756
00:34:24,590 --> 00:34:26,250
But she came at the right time.

757
00:34:26,300 --> 00:34:27,360
If she hadn't come,

758
00:34:28,960 --> 00:34:30,469
I would have been dead already.

759
00:34:30,469 --> 00:34:31,480
Am I too stupid,

760
00:34:32,070 --> 00:34:33,330
or are you being vague?

761
00:34:35,330 --> 00:34:36,659
You're just too stupid.

762
00:34:37,230 --> 00:34:38,560
You like her, don't you?

763
00:34:45,659 --> 00:34:47,659
Zhang San's Diary.

764
00:34:57,490 --> 00:34:59,620
Move that flower a bit more to the left.

765
00:35:00,140 --> 00:35:02,000
-A little more to the left.
-Okay.

766
00:35:03,110 --> 00:35:06,540
[The late Empress Dowager]

767
00:35:03,150 --> 00:35:04,750
Too much. Move it right a bit.

768
00:35:05,670 --> 00:35:07,220
Lift that grass up a little.

769
00:35:08,570 --> 00:35:10,100
Yes, a bit more to the right.

770
00:35:13,610 --> 00:35:14,550
Crown Prince.

771
00:35:17,290 --> 00:35:18,800
I pay my respects to you, Grandmother.

772
00:35:18,800 --> 00:35:20,450
May the Your Majesty be blessed.

773
00:35:20,450 --> 00:35:22,850
Why are you here

774
00:35:23,850 --> 00:35:25,370
instead of studying in the library?

775
00:35:25,370 --> 00:35:26,770
Grandmother,

776
00:35:27,330 --> 00:35:30,460
His Majesty canceled the Flower Festival
a few days ago.

777
00:35:30,520 --> 00:35:33,450
But I saw these hydrangeas blooming
so beautifully,

778
00:35:34,040 --> 00:35:36,700
and it would be a shame
to leave them unattended,

779
00:35:36,890 --> 00:35:38,820
so I thought I'd arrange them a bit.

780
00:35:39,520 --> 00:35:41,920
By the time of your birthday, Grandmother,

781
00:35:42,160 --> 00:35:43,700
they will be in full bloom.

782
00:35:45,730 --> 00:35:47,740
They can be a birthday gift for you.

783
00:35:50,520 --> 00:35:52,330
How thoughtful of you.

784
00:35:56,370 --> 00:35:57,250
However,

785
00:35:57,770 --> 00:36:00,590
I notice the arrangement of these flowers

786
00:36:01,560 --> 00:36:03,560
seems to have some special meaning.

787
00:36:05,190 --> 00:36:06,720
Take all these things away.

788
00:36:07,000 --> 00:36:08,200
You may leave for now.

789
00:36:08,200 --> 00:36:09,020
-Yes.
-Yes.

790
00:36:15,970 --> 00:36:17,650
You have a discerning eye, Grandmother.

791
00:36:17,650 --> 00:36:18,230
Look.

792
00:36:18,910 --> 00:36:21,370
This depicts two dragons
playing with a pearl,

793
00:36:21,370 --> 00:36:22,900
symbolizing good fortune.

794
00:36:22,970 --> 00:36:23,660
Absurd!

795
00:36:25,970 --> 00:36:28,810
Great Xia can only have one true dragon.

796
00:36:30,390 --> 00:36:31,770
Your mother died early,

797
00:36:32,200 --> 00:36:34,660
and the Emperor
has already found a new love.

798
00:36:34,930 --> 00:36:36,860
Soon he will appoint a new Empress.

799
00:36:38,160 --> 00:36:38,960
In the future,

800
00:36:39,040 --> 00:36:41,160
there may well be more Crown Princes.

801
00:36:42,810 --> 00:36:44,490
In this vast palace,

802
00:36:45,200 --> 00:36:46,530
with all its intrigues,

803
00:36:48,330 --> 00:36:51,110
only I truly care for you.

804
00:36:51,980 --> 00:36:53,040
Do you understand?

805
00:36:54,790 --> 00:36:56,560
You've misunderstood, Grandmother.

806
00:36:56,560 --> 00:36:58,020
The two dragons I planted—

807
00:36:58,370 --> 00:36:59,970
one represents you, Grandmother,

808
00:36:59,970 --> 00:37:01,230
and the other is me.

809
00:37:02,410 --> 00:37:04,600
You are the mother figure of the empire,

810
00:37:04,600 --> 00:37:06,130
presiding over the palace,

811
00:37:06,520 --> 00:37:08,330
supremely noble—

812
00:37:08,640 --> 00:37:11,040
the auspicious dragon protecting
the imperial family.

813
00:37:11,040 --> 00:37:12,550
I, with all my heart,

814
00:37:13,040 --> 00:37:13,770
only wish

815
00:37:14,160 --> 00:37:15,970
to be filial by your side

816
00:37:16,680 --> 00:37:18,800
and serve the empire,

817
00:37:19,480 --> 00:37:21,940
as the little dragon
under your protection.

818
00:37:28,520 --> 00:37:30,040
Come, get up.

819
00:37:35,080 --> 00:37:37,330
You truly are my good grandson.

820
00:37:40,560 --> 00:37:41,370
Rest assured,

821
00:37:42,560 --> 00:37:45,210
as long as I am around in this palace,

822
00:37:46,080 --> 00:37:47,410
those sordid affairs

823
00:37:48,080 --> 00:37:50,140
will not interfere with your future.

824
00:37:51,770 --> 00:37:53,290
You, my little dragon,

825
00:37:54,200 --> 00:37:56,410
are the only true dragon in this palace.

826
00:37:57,770 --> 00:37:58,830
Do you understand?

827
00:38:03,080 --> 00:38:04,480
Thank you, Grandmother.

828
00:38:12,260 --> 00:38:21,080
[SOS]

829
00:38:24,330 --> 00:38:25,600
If you are like me,

830
00:38:25,810 --> 00:38:26,870
leave me a message.

831
00:38:27,200 --> 00:38:28,420
I want to meet you.
